        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare low-grade astrocytoma characterized by superficial location in the cerebral hemispheres with involvement of the meninges composed of GFAP-expressing cells showing nuclear and cytoplasmic pleomorphism and xanthomatous change surrounded by a reticulin network. The tumor corresponds to WHO grade II and typically affects children and young adults who often present with a long history of seizures. Extent of resection and mitotic index are important prognostic factors."
        },
